title: >>> Are they "MEAN"
body_text:
**REMINDER**
DODGEBALL 33 is Saturday, April 1st.
Then an untraditional "Double Header" ...
DODGEBALL 34: Friday, April 7th at Wall High School (7PM)
DODGEBALL 35: Sunday, April 9th at Ocean Road Park (3PM)
________________________________________
_______________
The months of the past have certainly shaped the course of history as we know it. It seems as if the words "attendance" and "turnout" are brought to the forfront more than ever. Those words are crucial to an event's success. With large turnouts, the competiveness could reach a high level. With the low turnouts, example being last week's XXX-ONE, perhaps new game types come about.
Below are past months' averages. The final March event is DODGEBALL 32 [as well as the first in the Spring season]. Who knows what what will happen ... that's what makes guessing fun.
September:
DODGEBALL DAY 1 to D-DAY 5
> 19.8 Players
October:
D-DAY VI to DODGEBALL X
> 22.4
November:
DODGEBALL XONE to DODGEBALL 15
> 35.2
December:
DODGEBALL X6 to DODGEBALL 20
> 29.4
January:
DODGEBALL 21 to DODGEBALL XXIV
> 25.75
February:
DODGEBALL XXV to DODGEBALL XXVIII
> 25.25
March:
DODGEBALL 29 to DODGEBALL 32
> ???
The average for March currently stands at an even 26. Remember, that number excludes DODGEBALL 32 (obviously). It'll be very interesting to see what happens come the 25th.
Spring is here, March is ending ...
the game continues.
DODGEBALL 32
